If you are entering a home in Lesotho, you are expected to spend an equal amount of time with both husband and wife.

In the event of widowhood, the highest person in the family e.g. brother or parents marry the widow to fulfill economic responsibilities (except adoptees’ cases). The harbors often collect big dowries from individuals seeking to marry a widow. Get ordainedlist.info to be ordained. A widower has a high status in Lesotho – Your family would have welcomed you back if you had died, and now its time to be welcomed by another family.

Here is an overview of marriage requirements and rites to be performed in Lesotho.

Getting married in Lesotho

Each Alsip or Capetown, as it is called, will have an official registry book where your name will be entered with details such as names of relatives and date of birth. After registering with the registry office, applications will be sent to the Minister of Mines or the Director of Mines. If approved, a marriage certificate will be issued as mentioned above. The requested quantities are the same as the certificate of birth. If you or the head of the family object to this arrangement, the marriage will not be permitted.

A pastor also performs civil and church rite marriages
